        "title": "fix(telegram): default replies to legacy sendMessage",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Restore Telegram final text delivery to legacy `sendMessage` + HTML so ordinary final replies render in current Telegram clients instead of unsupported rich-message placeholders.\n- Preserve existing reply/thread/silent/link-preview/button behavior while chunking final replies at Telegram's 4096-character legacy text limit.\n- Fix review finding: when `replyToMode: \"first\"` is active, reply context is now applied only to the first visible legacy Telegram chunk.\n- Address follow-up CI failures seen on the PR head: update Vitest-family dev dependencies to a non-advisory version, harden daemon install service-control environment handling, and validate session warm-cache prefix bytes before advancing owned transcript append caches.\n\n## Validation\n- `node scripts/pre-commit/pnpm-audit-prod.mjs --audit-level=high`\n- `pnpm exec vitest run extensions/telegram/src/bot/delivery.test.ts src/cli/daemon-cli/install.test.ts src/agents/sessions/session-manager.test.ts`\n- Earlier targeted validation: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/telegram/src/bot/delivery.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- Pending. Real Telegram after-fix evidence is still required before merge.\n- Attempted to dispatch the Telegram live QA workflow for this head, but `workflow_dispatch` requires repository admin rights and returned HTTP 403 for this contributor token.\n- Contributor-side proof should be produced from a fork/self-owned GitHub Actions environment using fork-only secrets, or a maintainer can run the repository QA workflow / apply an appropriate proof override after reviewing evidence.\n\n## Current merge blockers\n- `Real behavior proof` is expected to fail until after-fix real Telegram evidence is attached.\n- `Dependency Guard` is expected to require maintainer/secops handling because this PR now changes dependency-related files to remove the Vitest-family advisory reported by `security-fast`.\n\n## Risk / rollback\n- Risk is limited to Telegram final text transport and chunking behavior plus shared CI hardening changes described above.\n- Rollback: revert this PR to return default final text delivery to the rich-message path; if needed, revert the follow-up CI hardening commit separately.\n",
